Package: qperm
Type: Package
Title: Quantum-Accelerated Sign-Flip Permutation Inference for Neuroimaging
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Kiju", "Lee", email = "kiju.lee22@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: One-sample and paired sign-flip permutation tests for group neuroimaging
    data with family-wise-error corrected p-values, offering a proposed quantum
    amplitude-estimation estimator alongside the classical permutation test. The quantum
    estimator is emulated in pure R and can optionally be run as real quantum circuits
    through 'Qiskit' via 'reticulate'. It is a simulation and a query-complexity
    demonstration, not a runtime speedup on classical hardware. Extends the quantum
    statistical bootstrap framework of Chen, Ma and Zhong (2026)
    <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2604.00951> to the max-over-voxels and cluster-extent statistics
    used for family-wise error control in functional MRI.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports: stats, graphics, utils
Suggests: reticulate, RNifti, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
URL: https://github.com/kikijuki/qperm
